<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-01-14T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-01-14T13:00:00-05:00" n="888" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d888">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/7209</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Collector <persName type="from">Cobb</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-01-14T11:00:00-07:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 14, 1916, 11 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>My January 13, 11 a.m. Train bringing employees American Smelting and
                            Refining Company and others from Chihuahua left there this morning 8.30
                            and should reach El Paso about dark.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Cobb</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>